Description: Fix CVE-2023-44271 (Pillow DoS via large text input to ImageFont)
 Backport of upstream commit 1fe1bb49c452b0318cad12ea9d97c3bef188e9a7
 (PR #7244, released in Pillow 10.0.0). Adds ImageFont.MAX_STRING_LENGTH
 (default 1,000,000) and a _string_length_check() helper that raises
 ValueError when text exceeds the limit. The check is invoked at the top
 of the ImageFont, FreeTypeFont and TransposedFont measurement/render
 methods that previously allocated unbounded memory for arbitrarily long
 text input (CWE-400 / CWE-770).
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/python-pillow/Pillow/commit/1fe1bb49c452b0318cad12ea9d97c3bef188e9a7
Bug: https://github.com/python-pillow/Pillow/pull/7244
Author: Andrew Murray <radarhere@users.noreply.github.com>
Last-Update: 2026-06-12

