CVE-2024-28219: Use strncpy to avoid buffer overflow in _imagingcms.c

In _imagingcms.c, a buffer overflow exists because strcpy is used
instead of strncpy. The mode_in / mode_out fields of CmsTransformObject
are 8-byte buffers, but cms_transform_new() copied caller-provided
strings into them with strcpy, allowing a buffer overflow when callers
pass mode strings longer than 7 characters via PIL.ImageCms.buildTransform
or buildProofTransform.

Upstream fix: https://github.com/python-pillow/Pillow/commit/2a93aba5cfcf6e241ab4f9392c13e3b74032c061
Advisory:    https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-44wm-f244-xhp3

NOTE on test fixture: the upstream commit also adds a 290-byte binary
ICC profile at Tests/icc/sGrey-v2-nano.icc which is referenced by the
new test_long_modes() test. GNU patch 2.8 does not support git binary
diffs, so the binary file is NOT included in this patch. If the test
fixture is required, copy Tests/icc/sGrey-v2-nano.icc verbatim from
the upstream Pillow repository (commit 2a93aba5) into the package tree.
The C source fix below (the actual security fix) is independent of the
test fixture and applies cleanly.

